cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.RO

The paper proposes a method based on convolutional neural networks for automatic detection and localisation of fetal standard views in freehand 2D ultrasound data. This involves image processing and machine learning, which are core topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions real-time operation and optimal output, which suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the use of bounding boxes for localisation indicates a potential connection to robotics (cs.RO).
